The two statements “(void) upload_data;” and “(void) upload_data_size;” are no-effect expressions (they merely evaluate and discard the parameter values). Their removal would not affect program behaviour, so they constitute dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (Note: if these objects were volatile or their evaluation had side‑effects, they would not be dead; here they are ordinary parameters.)
